    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-05-03T01:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-05-03T01:35:00-05:00" n="471"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363 Standard Oil/362: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kornfeld</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-05-03T10:00:00+03:25">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1924—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 3—5:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>36. Bill to ratify Sinclair contract was introduced in Mejliss by Prime Minister
                    on April 19th. I have learned from reliable source <pb facs="0640" n="546"
                        xml:id="pg_546"/> that a protest renewing the Khoshtaria claims has been
                    addressed to the Persian Government by the British.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kornfeld</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
